        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Hrlx5ar5-HQIOsnS16Cv-10" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: start;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;-apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif&quot; style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px; background-color: light-dark(#ffffff, var(--ge-dark-color, #121212));&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Not in architecture&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;padding-inline-start: 24px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, &amp;quot;system-ui&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(24, 24, 24);&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;No CDN / Load Balancer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— QR pages could get traffic spikes from marketing campaigns or press coverage. Cloud Run handles auto-scaling, but adding&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Cloud CDN&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for static assets (images, CSS, JS) would reduce latency and cost.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No caching layer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— Every QR scan currently hits Cloud SQL directly. Since QR traceability data rarely changes once written, it&#39;s very cache-friendly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Redis (Memorystore)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in front of the DB would cut read latency and DB load — mention as a future optimisation.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No backup / DR strategy shown&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— If Cloud SQL goes down, what&#39;s the recovery plan? The answer:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Cloud SQL has automated daily backups and point-in-time recovery built in&lt;/strong&gt;. Mention it verbally — you don&#39;t need it on the diagram, but you need to know it exists.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Auth details are thin&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— &quot;Hashed in secure place&quot; is vague. Be ready to say: passwords hashed with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;bcrypt&lt;/strong&gt;, sessions managed with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;JWT tokens&lt;/strong&gt;, or alternatively offload auth entirely to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Firebase Auth / Google Identity Platform&lt;/strong&gt;. Pick one and own it.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;No rate limiting&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— The public-facing QR API could be abused (scraping, DDoS). Mention&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Cloud Armor&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for DDoS protection or&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;API Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;with rate limiting policies — a one-sentence answer shows you&#39;ve thought about security beyond just authentication.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="185" width="1490" x="33.5" y="790" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
